cs.LO, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.SY. 

The paper deals with the decidability of the distributed version of the Ramadge and Wonham control problem, which involves automata theory and control theory. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the study of processes and communication, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the paper deals with controller synthesis, which is related to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
